    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup is anchored today by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (80.97), who both draw premium matchups against pitchers with xERAs exceeding 4.00. **Kyle Tucker** is our strongest play, bolstered by a 14% park factor boost and a favorable projection against Sugano. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from an optimal #1 spot and a slight SP skill advantage, making him an elite engine for runs and stolen bases. We are also looking for high-upside production from **Andy Pages** (75.58) and **Drake Baldwin** (72.00); both players benefit significantly from their respective park factors and the exploitable profiles of Walker and Sugano. While **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (57.07) faces the toughest matchup of the day against Webb, his dynamic platoon advantage helps maintain a viable floor for a team prioritizing speed.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (60.17) on the bench. Despite a solid score, he was ultimately edged out by the superior efficiency and platoon-adjusted upside of **Marcell Ozuna** and **Jackson Merrill** (65.58). We continue to keep a close eye on **Luis Robert Jr.** (50.66), who remains a high-variance play due to his speed profile but is currently benched as his projected daily efficiency lags behind our starters. Investors should note that nearly our entire lineup is subject to \"Lineup Pending\" status; specifically, we are relying on assumed batting positions for **Nolan Schanuel**, **Miguel Vargas**, and **Josh Lowe**. Should official lineups move **Josh Lowe** out of the #8 spot or alter the deployment of **Jacob Wilson** (68.59), we will need to monitor our aggregate team output closely to protect our game caps.",
